---
description: Context discovery from domain and L345 routers every turn
alwaysApply: true
---

Before planning, coding, testing, or MR work:

1. Run **Context Discovery** from `.cursor/context/l345_router.md` (standards, MR, recipe templates, agent authoring).
2. Run **Context Discovery** from `.cursor/context/router.md` (domain / product L2 — add domain `*.md` under `.cursor/context/` and wire topics in the router as the repo grows).
3. Load only the agent sections identified by those routers, then proceed.
4. At response end, prepend the project interaction log per `lsai_superagent.md` § **Recipe — Project interaction log (every turn)** at `~/data/{project_slug}/runs/{run_slug}/interaction_log.md` — read entire file first; **Prepend algorithm**; never truncate.
5. **New project:** **`bash .cursor/scripts/copy_template.sh <dest> --bootstrap`** (excludes `.git`). **Existing checkout:** **`bash .cursor/scripts/bootstrap_portable.sh`** — one shot; do not duplicate in chat.
